{"format":"tiptap/v1","updatedAt":"2026-06-21T13:54:49.014Z","doc":{"type":"doc","content":[{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":2},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"What It Is"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"The Context Editing Tool"},{"type":"text","text":" is Anthropic's API capability that "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"automatically removes stale tool calls and results from the context window"},{"type":"text","text":" when approaching token limits. Unlike manual compaction (which summarizes conversation history), context editing "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"selectively clears specific content"},{"type":"text","text":" while preserving conversation flow."}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Key difference from compaction"},{"type":"text","text":":\n- "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Compaction"},{"type":"text","text":": Summarizes all previous messages → lossy compression\n- "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Context Editing"},{"type":"text","text":": Removes only stale tool uses/results → precise deletion"}]},{"type":"horizontalRule"},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":2},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Why It Matters"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"For "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"agentic workflows"},{"type":"text","text":" (like your distributed systems engineering), tool accumulation is the biggest context killer:"}]},{"type":"codeBlock","attrs":{"language":"yaml"},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Turn 1: [read_file: auth.ts] → 8,000 tokens\nTurn 2: [grep: \"error\"] → 1,200 tokens  \nTurn 3: [test_run: auth.test.ts] → 4,500 tokens\nTurn 4: [read_file: guard.ts] → 7,200 tokens\n...\nTotal: 100+ tool results → 180k tokens"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Without context editing"},{"ty